From e009fd5fc1384b083c62937618a281db14859642 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ben <bb569@scarletmail.rutgers.edu>
Date: Tue, 5 Aug 2025 23:18:11 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Add support for modern GROMACS 2024.4+ with gmxapi
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Update Driver.cpp to use modern gmxapi instead of deprecated CommandLineModuleManager
- Add support for TPR-based workflow execution via gmxapi::fromTprFile()
- Maintain backward compatibility with legacy GROMACS versions
- Fix include paths and library linking for external GROMACS installations
- Add FindGROMACS.cmake module for better GROMACS detection
- Support C++17 standard required by modern GROMACS
- Link against both libgromacs and libgmxapi libraries

This enables SSAGES to build and work with GROMACS 2024.4 and newer versions
while maintaining compatibility with older GROMACS installations.

Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
